### ============================================================
### VitalSignController - API Tests
### Base URL: http://localhost:8080/api/v1/vitalsign
### ============================================================

### [1] POST record vitals - normal readings
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/vitalsign/recordvital
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Role: CNA

{
  "taskId": 1,
  "residentId": 1,
  "bloodPressureSystolic": 120,
  "bloodPressureDiastolic": 80,
  "heartRateBpm": 72,
  "spo2Percentage": 98,
  "temperatureFahrenheit": 98.6,
  "respiratoryRate": 16,
  "painScale": 2,
  "notes": "Resident calm and cooperative"
}

###

### [2] POST record vitals - abnormal readings (high BP, low SpO2)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/vitalsign/recordvital
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Role: NURSE

{
  "taskId": 2,
  "residentId": 2,
  "bloodPressureSystolic": 180,
  "bloodPressureDiastolic": 110,
  "heartRateBpm": 105,
  "spo2Percentage": 88,
  "temperatureFahrenheit": 101.2,
  "respiratoryRate": 24,
  "painScale": 7,
  "notes": "Resident complained of chest tightness. RN notified."
}

###

### [3] POST record vitals - no taskId (standalone vital recording)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/vitalsign/recordvital
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Role: CNA

{
  "taskId": null,
  "residentId": 3,
  "bloodPressureSystolic": 130,
  "bloodPressureDiastolic": 85,
  "heartRateBpm": 78,
  "spo2Percentage": 96,
  "temperatureFahrenheit": 99.1,
  "respiratoryRate": 18,
  "painScale": 0,
  "notes": null
}

###

